# Project image/video assets — only the production-ready encodings
# (AVIF + JPG fallback + .web.mp4) ship in git so Vercel can serve them
# without an external CDN. The bulky source files (raw PNGs, raw MP4s,
# MOVs) stay local on the designer's machine and are excluded by the
# patterns below. `scripts/optimize-assets.mjs` and `optimize-videos.mjs`
# regenerate the production encodings from sources when they change.
public/images/**/*.png
public/images/**/*.mp4
public/images/**/*.mov
public/images/**/*.m4v
public/images/**/*.webm
!public/images/**/*.web.mp4

# Windows / macOS file-explorer artefacts that sneak into public/
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# We use pnpm; npm lockfile must not coexist
package-lock.json

# Claude Skills installed at project root (not project source)
skills/
